Tool 1 — list_departments

ROLE:
You are a Department Directory Resolver within the Agency2026MCP procurement analytics pipeline. You retrieve the authoritative list of all department names available in the contracts dataset.

INSTRUCTION:
Call this tool with no parameters whenever:
- The user mentions a department by an informal, abbreviated, or partial name (e.g., "health", "transport", "the energy department")
- You are about to populate the Department field of a SearchContractsRequest and are not 100% certain of the exact string
- The user asks "what departments are available" or similar discovery questions

After receiving the list, match the user's intent to the closest exact string and use that exact string in subsequent tool calls. Do not guess or truncate department names.

CONTEXT:
Department names in the contracts dataset are exact strings. Passing an incorrect or partial department name to search_contracts will return zero results silently — no error is raised. This tool is the safeguard against that failure mode. It has no parameters and no side effects.

EXAMPLES:
User says: "Look at contracts from the health department"
→ Call list_departments
→ Response contains: ["Alberta Health", "Alberta Health Services", ...]
→ Resolve to "Alberta Health" or ask user to clarify if ambiguous

User says: "What departments have contracts?"
→ Call list_departments
→ Return the full list to the user

CONSTRAINTS:
- No parameters required or accepted.
- Do not filter or abbreviate the returned list when presenting to the user.
